Validated that:

Is available for MA and GHP Line of Business (LOB)
Clinical Consultation will function accordingly with all its components after a beneficiary is selected by the user.
Data displayed should be the following:
Location: Requesting Provider
Scenario 1
If a user hasn't selected a provider or removes it from the "Provider Search" and presses the "Next" button, the "No provider has been selected" message from the selection box will be displayed in red lettering. (Only applies for Web Version)
Image
The "Provider Search" field will be displayed red around triggering the field to be used for the user to select a provider.
Image
Scenario 2
If the data entered by the user doesn't match any results from the "Provider Search",the search grid will close, and an error message will be displayed below the "Provider Search" in red lettering. The error will be configurable and display the following message: "No results were found for the search criteria provided".
The "Provider Search" field will be displayed red around triggering the field with the error.
Image
The "Next" button will be displayed as disabled and will be clickable when required information is incomplete in the corresponding section.
Image
Mobile Version:
For the alerts from Scenario 1, the validations messages will be triggered for the scenario a user removes required components for the completion of the step after a step is completed.
The alerts will be triggered for the section when the user presses "Submit" in the "Consultation Review" step of the process.
For more detailed information, see "PBI-72324".
Mockup images are not final and are subject to change.
Responsiveness
Functionalities are working as expected for the following resolutions:
1920x1080, 1366x768, 1280x720, 390x844, 1440x900, 1280x1024
Colors & Fonts are in accordance with URL/Screenshot attached (detail of colors/fonts)
All static elements on the screen must have fixed ID, which will be used for Automation Purposes
Log Action
When the button is pressed, save action to Action Log, include the following:
auditEventType: RequestingProviderNextClickError
auditEventGroup: Clinical Consultation
applicationDomain: Provider Portal
User
Event Data:
BeneficiaryName
BeneficiaryId
EventDate
Field Name + Error Message
